                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.61/890: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T23:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 29, 1940—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 29—8:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>600. Embassy’s telegram No. 584, May 25.<note n="4" xml:id="d644fn4">Not
                        printed.</note> A Tass despatch was issued tonight stating that Molotov has
                    instructed Maiski to advise the British Government that the proposed mission to
                    Moscow of Sir Stafford Cripps is unacceptable to the Soviet Government and that
                    if the British Government desires to conduct trade negotiations with the Soviet
                    Government “and not simply confine itself to talk of a nonexistent change in the
                    relations between England and the Soviet Union” it can do so through its
                    Ambassador at Moscow, Mr. William Seeds,<note n="5" xml:id="d644fn5">Sir William
                        Seeds, British Ambassador to the Soviet Union since January 1939, who left
                        after the outbreak of the Finnish-Soviet war.</note> or in the event that he
                    is not returning to his post, through his successor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
